# Brief Description of CSS Properties

## Margin

Defines the space outside the border of an element. It can be set for all four sides or individually for top, right,
bottom, and left.

## Padding

Defines the space inside the border of an element, between the border and the content. It can be set for all four sides
or individually for top, right, bottom, and left.

## Border

Specifies the style, width, and color of the border around an element.

## Box-shadow

Adds shadow effects to an element's frame. It can take values for horizontal offset, vertical offset, blur radius,
spread radius, and color.

## Text-shadow

Adds shadow effects to text. It can take values for horizontal offset, vertical offset, blur radius, and color.

## Background-image

Sets one or more background images for an element. The images can be specified by a URL.

## Font-size

Sets the size of the font. It can be specified in various units like pixels (px), ems (em), percentages (%), etc.

## Font-style

Specifies the style of the font. It can be normal, italic, or oblique.

## Text-transform

Controls the capitalization of text. It can be set to none, capitalize, uppercase, or lowercase.
